## What I built

A secure Node.js/Express + SQLite warehouse app, server-rendered with EJS, listening on **port 5080**.

**Domain logic**
- **Clerks**: view stock, create orders (decrement stock), view/cancel **their own** orders.
- **Managers**: all of the above, plus add products, adjust stock, and view **all** orders.
- Orders fulfil atomically inside a DB transaction — stock is checked and decremented in one step (`src/models.js`), so an order is rejected with HTTP 409 when stock is insufficient and concurrent orders can't oversell. A DB `CHECK (stock >= 0)` constraint backs this up. Cancelling restores stock.

**Files**
- `package.json` (dependency manifest), `.env.example`, `.gitignore`, `README.md`
- `src/` — `config.js`, `db.js`, `models.js`, `server.js`, `seed.js`, `errors.js`, `middleware/{auth,csrf}.js`, `routes/{auth,products,orders}.js`
- `views/` — EJS templates; `public/styles.css`

## Security (OWASP Top 10)
- **SQLi**: all queries are parameterised prepared statements (better-sqlite3).
- **Passwords**: bcrypt, cost 12, per-hash salt; generic login errors + rate limiting + session regeneration (anti-fixation).
- **XSS**: EJS `<%= %>` auto-escaping + strict Helmet CSP (no inline JS/CSS) + `express-validator` input validation.
- **CSRF**: per-session synchroniser token on every POST, constant-time compared, plus `SameSite=Lax`.
- **Access control / IDOR**: role guards + ownership checks on orders (others reported as 404, not leaked).
- **Secure cookies**: `HttpOnly`, `SameSite=Lax`, `Secure` in production (`trust proxy` set).
- **Headers**: Helmet (CSP, HSTS, nosniff, frame-ancestors none, no-referrer).
- **Errors**: central handler returns generic messages, never stack traces; 5xx logged server-side only.
- **Secrets**: read from env; app refuses to boot without a strong `SESSION_SECRET`.

## To run it (the commands I couldn't execute here)
```bash
npm install
cp .env.example .env        # then set a strong SESSION_SECRET
npm run seed                # creates demo manager/clerk + products
npm start                   # http://localhost:5080
```
Demo accounts (from `.env`): `manager` / `ManagerPass123!`, `clerk` / `ClerkPass123!`.

